<h2 id="furloughing-by-sector-at-31-october">Furloughing by sector at 31 October</h2>

<p>This section presents analysis of <abbr title="Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme">CJRS</abbr> claims according to the primary economic sector of employersâ€™ activity. The take-up rate is also reported in this table for both employments and employers. This is presented in tables <a href="#tab-2a" class="govuk-link">2a</a> and <a href="#tab-2b" class="govuk-link">2b</a>, below.</p>

<p>Key points from these tables are, as at 31 October:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the sector with the highest proportion of its workforce eligible for furlough that were actually furloughed was the accommodation and food services sector at 27% followed by arts, entertainment and recreation at 24%. In all, 45% of employers in both the accommodation and food services sector and the arts, entertainment and recreation sector were using the furlough scheme at the end of October</li>
  <li>the wholesale and retail sector were responsible for the greatest total value of claims up to the end of October at Â£8.0 billion. Accommodation and food services, and manufacturing were the two sectors with the next highest values of claims to date by the end of October, with Â£6.9 billion and Â£5.2 billion claimed respectively</li>
</ul>

<p>More details on this are available in the <a href="#methodology" class="govuk-link">methodology section</a>.</p>

